      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS KOMMUNICATION (4) is yet to win but has kicked off her career in promising fashion with three placings from four starts. Registered yet another strong performance last time when she battled on bravely to finish second over 1609m at Cranbourne. Good enough to win a race of this calibre. GALHALLA (1) finished third on debut last start despite copping a check and galloping, beaten 14 metres over 1690m at this circuit. Big chance again in a similar assignment. GREAT HORIZON (3) is a great chance after a string of sound recent performances, the latest a solid fourth at Bendigo over 2150m. Hard to find fault. ALDEBARAN DENBAY (8) was out of the money two runs ago then broke and finished fifth last start over 1690m at this course, coming home 30 metres from the winner. Can feature if he behaves.",
